commentary: Shahid Afridi to Tikolo, OUT Tikolo fails again. He went down the track, first side stepped towards leg before trying to move across towards the line and went for the lofted hit. But Afridi had held this one back and Tikolo was through early with the shot. The ball slid through the bat and pad gap and fell on the stumps. Afridi's index finger shoots up towards the sky. The Kenyan legend walks back to the hut.

commentary: Shahid Afridi to Obuya, OUT Wicket no 5 for the captain! Obuya's entertaining knock is over. Afridi teased him with a flighted delivery and he couldn't resist going for the big hit but he couldn't clear long-on. 5 for 16! ooh la la!

commentary: Shahid Afridi to Odhiambo, OUT And then they were one. This one rolled off the pad to the on side. Confusion. Chaos. The striker rushed down the track but his partner wasn't going anywhere. There is a direct hit at the striker's end - shouldn't he have lobbed it safely to hands of a fielder close to the stumps? - and there is no batsman in sight near that end. Gone. Terrible.

commentary: Umar Gul to Ngoche, OUT Oh dear! He shouldered arms there, only to hear the death rattle. It landed on a  length just outside off and skidded in. The batsman left it alone. Mistake. Clatter!
